I once saw a very nice original white/white 66 or 67 deluxe with what looked 
like a factory installed so 42 westy kit in it.   
  Ya, check the M codes.  Check under the Z bed to see if the rear seat has 
the side hold down screw piece welded into the body.  

I though clam shells were earlier than the so 42 kit.  That so 42s and so 44s 
had the rectangular light covers, that in cross section are a U

the westys z bed should have a tag on it near the floor by the side doors- it 
would say what year  on the tag- that the kit was made.

IN any case, enjoy the bus  :)
